      "content": "thanks, this is getting better. but i'm noticing that even when you're explaining these points, they feel a bit like you're just summarizing a textbook. for a competitive debate, my students need to know the moral and philosophical weight behind these arguments—not just the mechanics. like, how do proponents frame the ethical obligation of a state to its own citizens over non-citizens? if they can grasp the \"moral necessity\" aspect of the argument, they can argue it with more conviction. can you expand on that philosophical dimension?",
